[2026-03-18T11:43:48.513Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Y4r1bNFPzZqiqAKueG3zeY","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary report of the event processing pipeline. Let me compile all the information I've gathered:\n\n## Event Processing Pipeline Analysis\n\nI've conducted a thorough exploration of the event processing pipeline in the personas-cloud codebase. Here's what I found:\n\n### 1. **persona_events Table Schema**\n\nLocated in: `/packages/orchestrator/src/db/schema.ts` (lines 121-136)\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS persona_events (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  project_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default',\n  event_type TEXT NOT NULL,\n  source_type TEXT NOT NULL,\n  source_id TEXT,\n  target_persona_id TEXT,\n  payload TEXT,\n  status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending',\n  error_message TEXT,\n  processed_at TEXT,\n  use_case_id TEXT,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL\n);\n```\n\n**Indices:**\n- `idx_pe_status` on `status`\n- `idx_pe_created_status` on `(created_at, status)`\n- `idx_pe_project` on `project_id`\n\n### 2. **Event Processing Pipeline - eventProcessor.ts**\n\nLocated in: `/packages/orchestrator/src/eventProcessor.ts`\n\nThis is the core event processing module with three main functions:\n\n**Key Components:**\n\n- **Orphaned Event Recovery** (`recoverOrphanedEvents`): At startup, resets any events stuck in 'processing' state back to 'pending'\n  \n- **Stale Event Reaper** (`reapStaleEvents`): Periodic process (every 30 ticks at 2s interval ≈ 60s) that resets events stuck in 'processing' state longer than 120 seconds\n  \n- **Event Bus Tick** (`eventBusTick`, lines 103-244): The main event processing loop that:\n  - Fetches up to 50 pending events\n  - Wraps processing in a transaction\n  - **Phase 1**: Marks events as 'processing', matches against subscriptions, identifies affected personas\n  - **Phase 2**: Batch-fetches personas, tools, and running execution counts (2-3 queries total)\n  - **Phase 3**: Dispatches using Map lookups with in-tick concurrency tracking\n\n**Concurrency Management** (lines 175-182):\n- Tracks `running` executions from DB: `runningMap.get(persona.id) ?? 0`\n- Tracks `tickClaimed` from current tick: `claimed.get(persona.id) ?? 0`\n- Checks: `running + tickClaimed >= persona.maxConcurrent`\n- If over limit, event stays `pending` for retry on next tick\n\n### 3. **Event Status Enum/Types**\n\nLocated in: `/packages/shared/src/types.ts` (lines 106-119)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface PersonaEvent {\n  id: string;\n  projectId: string;\n  eventType: string;\n  sourceType: string;\n  sourceId: string | null;\n  targetPersonaId: string | null;\n  payload: string | null;\n  status: string;\n  errorMessage: string | null;\n  processedAt: string | null;\n  useCaseId: string | null;\n  createdAt: string;\n}\n```\n\n**Event Status Values** (from eventProcessor.ts):\n- `'pending'` - Initial state, ready for processing\n- `'processing'` - Currently being evaluated for dispatch (marked at start of tick)\n- `'skipped'` - No matching subscriptions found\n- `'delivered'` - All matches successfully dispatched, no failures or throttling\n- `'partial'` - Some matches delivered, but some failed (line 228)\n- `'failed'` - All matches failed (line 235: \"All subscription matches failed\")\n\n**Status Transitions** (lines 225-236):\n```\npending → processing → [\n  'skipped' (no matches),\n  'delivered' (all delivered, no fails/throttle),\n  'partial' (delivered > 0 AND (failed > 0 OR throttled > 0)),\n  'pending' (all throttled, reset for retry),\n  'failed' (all failed)\n]\n```\n\n### 4. **Existing Retry Logic**\n\n**Event-Level Retries:**\n- Concurrency throttling: Events remain `pending` when persona hits maxConcurrent limit (automatic retry next tick)\n- No explicit event-level retry count or backoff\n\n**Execution-Level Retries** (from dispatcher.ts):\n- Worker disconnect retries: Up to `MAX_DISCONNECT_RETRIES = 2` (line 19)\n- Tracks `disconnectRetries` in ActiveExecution (line 36)\n- Re-queues execution after worker disconnect if retries remain\n- Re-marking as 'queued' with error message showing retry count\n\n**Execution Tracking** (from schema.ts, lines 182-183):\n```sql\nretry_of_execution_id TEXT,\nretry_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n```\n\n### 5. **bus.ts File**\n\nLocated in: `/packages/shared/src/bus.ts`\n\nCore event matching logic with interfaces:\n\n**EventMatch interface** (lines 7-15):\n```typescript\nexport interface EventMatch {\n  eventId: string;\n  eventType: string;\n  subscriptionId: string;\n  personaId: string;\n  payload: string | null;\n  sourceId: string | null;\n  useCaseId: string | null;\n}\n```\n\n**matchEvent function** (lines 27-46): Matches single event against subscription list with rules:\n1. If `event.targetPersonaId` is set, only that persona's subscriptions match\n2. If `subscription.sourceFilter` is set, `event.sourceId` must match (exact or wildcard with `*`)\n\n**sourceFilterMatches function** (lines 52-60): Implements prefix wildcard matching for source filtering\n\n### 6. **protocol.ts File**\n\nLocated in: `/packages/shared/src/protocol.ts`\n\nWebSocket protocol definitions between orchestrator and workers, includes:\n- Worker messages (stdout, stderr, complete, event, progress, heartbeat, busy)\n- Orchestrator messages (ack, assign, cancel, shutdown, heartbeat)\n- Runtime validators for both message types\n- Serialization/deserialization helpers\n\n### 7. **Database Abstraction - events.ts**\n\nLocated in: `/packages/orchestrator/src/db/events.ts`\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `publishEvent()` - Creates new event with 'pending' status\n- `getPendingEvents()` - Fetches up to N pending events\n- `updateEventStatus()` - Updates status and processed_at timestamp\n- `resetStaleProcessingEvents()` - Reset events stuck in 'processing' > maxAgeSeconds\n- `resetAllProcessingEvents()` - Reset all processing events (used at startup)\n- `updateEventWithMetadata()` - Update status while preserving/updating payload\n\n### 8. **Concurrency Search Results**\n\nFound 19 files with 'concurrency' references (mostly in worktrees, but main: eventProcessor.ts, types.ts):\n- **types.ts (line 15)**: `maxConcurrent: number` in Persona interface\n- **eventProcessor.ts (lines 175-182)**: In-tick concurrency check comparing `running + tickClaimed >= persona.maxConcurrent`\n\n### 9. **Failed/Partial Status Handling**\n\n**Failed Event Status** (eventProcessor.ts, line 235):\n- Set when: `failed > 0 && delivered === 0 && throttled === 0`\n- Error message: \"All subscription matches failed\"\n- Reason: All dispatch attempts threw exceptions\n\n**Partial Event Status** (eventProcessor.ts, line 228):\n- Set when: `delivered > 0 && (failed > 0 || throttled > 0)`\n- Indicates: Mixed success/failure across subscription matches\n- At least one persona executed, but not all succeeded\n\n**Retention Handling** (retention.ts, lines 218-227):\n- Events with status NOT IN ('pending', 'processing') are purged after retention period\n- Stuck pending/processing events purged after 7x retention period (safety net)\n- Events classified as 'ephemeral' in TABLE_REGISTRY\n\n### 10. **Key Entry Points**\n\n- **startEventProcessor()** (eventProcessor.ts, line 67): Main entry point, starts 2-second interval tick loop\n- **startRetentionJob()** (retention.ts, line 34): Daily retention cleanup job\n- **publishEvent()** (db/events.ts, line 40): External callers publish events here\n- **getSubscriptionsByEventType()** (db/events.ts, line 169): Fetch subscriptions for event matching\n\n### 11. **Transaction Safety**\n\nThe entire event processing tick runs in a single database transaction (lines 118-238 of eventProcessor.ts) to:\n- Prevent partial updates in case of crashes\n- Maintain consistency between event status, matches, and dispatches\n- Dispatch requests queued in `pendingDispatches` array are fired AFTER transaction commits\n\n### Absolute File Paths\n\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/db/schema.ts` - Table definitions\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/db/events.ts` - Event CRUD operations\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/eventProcessor.ts` - Core event processing pipeline\n- `/packages/shared/src/types.ts` - Type definitions\n- `/packages/shared/src/bus.ts` - Event matching logic\n- `/packages/shared/src/protocol.ts` - WebSocket protocol\n- `/packages/shared/src/tableRegistry.ts` - Table lifecycle classification\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/retention.ts` - Data retention and cleanup\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/dispatcher.ts` - Execution dispatch and retry logic"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a4b35d37d12123e02 (use SendMessage with to: 'a4b35d37d12123e02' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 58500\ntool_uses: 20\nduration_ms: 50124</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"43babe3f-d692-4a25-8476-901485a68cf5","uuid":"ae54508c-9666-4c47-8a1d-5dfdfcf748f2","timestamp":"2026-03-18T11:43:48.407Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore this codebase thoroughly to understand the event processing pipeline. I need to find:\n\n1. The persona_events table schema/migration - look in packages/orchestrator/src/db/ and any migration files\n2. The eventProcessor.ts or eventBusTick.ts file that processes events - look for concurrency checks, where events get marked as failed/partial\n3. The event status enum/types - look in packages/shared/src/types.ts and related files\n4. Any retry logic that already exists\n5. The bus.ts file in packages/shared/src/bus.ts\n6. The protocol.ts file in packages/shared/src/protocol.ts\n\nSearch for:\n- \"concurrency\" references across the codebase\n- \"failed\" or \"partial\" status handling in event processing\n- \"persona_events\" table references\n- Any existing retry patterns\n\nBe very thorough - read all relevant files completely.","agentId":"a4b35d37d12123e02","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary report of the event processing pipeline. Let me compile all the information I've gathered:\n\n## Event Processing Pipeline Analysis\n\nI've conducted a thorough exploration of the event processing pipeline in the personas-cloud codebase. Here's what I found:\n\n### 1. **persona_events Table Schema**\n\nLocated in: `/packages/orchestrator/src/db/schema.ts` (lines 121-136)\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS persona_events (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  project_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default',\n  event_type TEXT NOT NULL,\n  source_type TEXT NOT NULL,\n  source_id TEXT,\n  target_persona_id TEXT,\n  payload TEXT,\n  status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending',\n  error_message TEXT,\n  processed_at TEXT,\n  use_case_id TEXT,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL\n);\n```\n\n**Indices:**\n- `idx_pe_status` on `status`\n- `idx_pe_created_status` on `(created_at, status)`\n- `idx_pe_project` on `project_id`\n\n### 2. **Event Processing Pipeline - eventProcessor.ts**\n\nLocated in: `/packages/orchestrator/src/eventProcessor.ts`\n\nThis is the core event processing module with three main functions:\n\n**Key Components:**\n\n- **Orphaned Event Recovery** (`recoverOrphanedEvents`): At startup, resets any events stuck in 'processing' state back to 'pending'\n  \n- **Stale Event Reaper** (`reapStaleEvents`): Periodic process (every 30 ticks at 2s interval ≈ 60s) that resets events stuck in 'processing' state longer than 120 seconds\n  \n- **Event Bus Tick** (`eventBusTick`, lines 103-244): The main event processing loop that:\n  - Fetches up to 50 pending events\n  - Wraps processing in a transaction\n  - **Phase 1**: Marks events as 'processing', matches against subscriptions, identifies affected personas\n  - **Phase 2**: Batch-fetches personas, tools, and running execution counts (2-3 queries total)\n  - **Phase 3**: Dispatches using Map lookups with in-tick concurrency tracking\n\n**Concurrency Management** (lines 175-182):\n- Tracks `running` executions from DB: `runningMap.get(persona.id) ?? 0`\n- Tracks `tickClaimed` from current tick: `claimed.get(persona.id) ?? 0`\n- Checks: `running + tickClaimed >= persona.maxConcurrent`\n- If over limit, event stays `pending` for retry on next tick\n\n### 3. **Event Status Enum/Types**\n\nLocated in: `/packages/shared/src/types.ts` (lines 106-119)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface PersonaEvent {\n  id: string;\n  projectId: string;\n  eventType: string;\n  sourceType: string;\n  sourceId: string | null;\n  targetPersonaId: string | null;\n  payload: string | null;\n  status: string;\n  errorMessage: string | null;\n  processedAt: string | null;\n  useCaseId: string | null;\n  createdAt: string;\n}\n```\n\n**Event Status Values** (from eventProcessor.ts):\n- `'pending'` - Initial state, ready for processing\n- `'processing'` - Currently being evaluated for dispatch (marked at start of tick)\n- `'skipped'` - No matching subscriptions found\n- `'delivered'` - All matches successfully dispatched, no failures or throttling\n- `'partial'` - Some matches delivered, but some failed (line 228)\n- `'failed'` - All matches failed (line 235: \"All subscription matches failed\")\n\n**Status Transitions** (lines 225-236):\n```\npending → processing → [\n  'skipped' (no matches),\n  'delivered' (all delivered, no fails/throttle),\n  'partial' (delivered > 0 AND (failed > 0 OR throttled > 0)),\n  'pending' (all throttled, reset for retry),\n  'failed' (all failed)\n]\n```\n\n### 4. **Existing Retry Logic**\n\n**Event-Level Retries:**\n- Concurrency throttling: Events remain `pending` when persona hits maxConcurrent limit (automatic retry next tick)\n- No explicit event-level retry count or backoff\n\n**Execution-Level Retries** (from dispatcher.ts):\n- Worker disconnect retries: Up to `MAX_DISCONNECT_RETRIES = 2` (line 19)\n- Tracks `disconnectRetries` in ActiveExecution (line 36)\n- Re-queues execution after worker disconnect if retries remain\n- Re-marking as 'queued' with error message showing retry count\n\n**Execution Tracking** (from schema.ts, lines 182-183):\n```sql\nretry_of_execution_id TEXT,\nretry_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n```\n\n### 5. **bus.ts File**\n\nLocated in: `/packages/shared/src/bus.ts`\n\nCore event matching logic with interfaces:\n\n**EventMatch interface** (lines 7-15):\n```typescript\nexport interface EventMatch {\n  eventId: string;\n  eventType: string;\n  subscriptionId: string;\n  personaId: string;\n  payload: string | null;\n  sourceId: string | null;\n  useCaseId: string | null;\n}\n```\n\n**matchEvent function** (lines 27-46): Matches single event against subscription list with rules:\n1. If `event.targetPersonaId` is set, only that persona's subscriptions match\n2. If `subscription.sourceFilter` is set, `event.sourceId` must match (exact or wildcard with `*`)\n\n**sourceFilterMatches function** (lines 52-60): Implements prefix wildcard matching for source filtering\n\n### 6. **protocol.ts File**\n\nLocated in: `/packages/shared/src/protocol.ts`\n\nWebSocket protocol definitions between orchestrator and workers, includes:\n- Worker messages (stdout, stderr, complete, event, progress, heartbeat, busy)\n- Orchestrator messages (ack, assign, cancel, shutdown, heartbeat)\n- Runtime validators for both message types\n- Serialization/deserialization helpers\n\n### 7. **Database Abstraction - events.ts**\n\nLocated in: `/packages/orchestrator/src/db/events.ts`\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `publishEvent()` - Creates new event with 'pending' status\n- `getPendingEvents()` - Fetches up to N pending events\n- `updateEventStatus()` - Updates status and processed_at timestamp\n- `resetStaleProcessingEvents()` - Reset events stuck in 'processing' > maxAgeSeconds\n- `resetAllProcessingEvents()` - Reset all processing events (used at startup)\n- `updateEventWithMetadata()` - Update status while preserving/updating payload\n\n### 8. **Concurrency Search Results**\n\nFound 19 files with 'concurrency' references (mostly in worktrees, but main: eventProcessor.ts, types.ts):\n- **types.ts (line 15)**: `maxConcurrent: number` in Persona interface\n- **eventProcessor.ts (lines 175-182)**: In-tick concurrency check comparing `running + tickClaimed >= persona.maxConcurrent`\n\n### 9. **Failed/Partial Status Handling**\n\n**Failed Event Status** (eventProcessor.ts, line 235):\n- Set when: `failed > 0 && delivered === 0 && throttled === 0`\n- Error message: \"All subscription matches failed\"\n- Reason: All dispatch attempts threw exceptions\n\n**Partial Event Status** (eventProcessor.ts, line 228):\n- Set when: `delivered > 0 && (failed > 0 || throttled > 0)`\n- Indicates: Mixed success/failure across subscription matches\n- At least one persona executed, but not all succeeded\n\n**Retention Handling** (retention.ts, lines 218-227):\n- Events with status NOT IN ('pending', 'processing') are purged after retention period\n- Stuck pending/processing events purged after 7x retention period (safety net)\n- Events classified as 'ephemeral' in TABLE_REGISTRY\n\n### 10. **Key Entry Points**\n\n- **startEventProcessor()** (eventProcessor.ts, line 67): Main entry point, starts 2-second interval tick loop\n- **startRetentionJob()** (retention.ts, line 34): Daily retention cleanup job\n- **publishEvent()** (db/events.ts, line 40): External callers publish events here\n- **getSubscriptionsByEventType()** (db/events.ts, line 169): Fetch subscriptions for event matching\n\n### 11. **Transaction Safety**\n\nThe entire event processing tick runs in a single database transaction (lines 118-238 of eventProcessor.ts) to:\n- Prevent partial updates in case of crashes\n- Maintain consistency between event status, matches, and dispatches\n- Dispatch requests queued in `pendingDispatches` array are fired AFTER transaction commits\n\n### Absolute File Paths\n\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/db/schema.ts` - Table definitions\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/db/events.ts` - Event CRUD operations\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/eventProcessor.ts` - Core event processing pipeline\n- `/packages/shared/src/types.ts` - Type definitions\n- `/packages/shared/src/bus.ts` - Event matching logic\n- `/packages/shared/src/protocol.ts` - WebSocket protocol\n- `/packages/shared/src/tableRegistry.ts` - Table lifecycle classification\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/retention.ts` - Data retention and cleanup\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/dispatcher.ts` - Execution dispatch and retry logic"}],"totalDurationMs":50124,"totalTokens":58500,"totalToolUseCount":20,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2083,"cache_read_input_tokens":54040,"output_tokens":2373,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2083},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
